Universities of the EDUC Alliance defined a common framework of objectives for Open Science , which includes the fields of research infrastructure, research data, citizen science and research evaluation. To develop and promote its own institutional strategy, the university has appointed the Commission for Open Science Policies , which collaborates with the Commission for Open Access to Scientific Literature on Open Access Policies. In 2024, UNICA adopted the \"University Policy for Open Science\" . The University of Cagliari has joined the CoARA coalition and signed the San Francisco DORA declaration, initiatives both related to research assessment. Open access to publications UniCa pursues the aims of open access: - through the establishment and maintenance of the institutional archive of the UNICA IRIS research products; - through the publishing services of its own publishing house, UNICApress , and the management of the UniCA Open Journals platform; - through incentives and facilitated conditions for open access publishing with scientific publishers (such as transformative contracts , as well as other discounts and agreements ). In 2022, the University's policies on open access to scientific research were approved: the basic concepts were set out, as well as the definitions and the practices to be followed in order to comply with Open Access publication standards. Open science: learn more Open Science event on 27 October 2023 Open Access event on 26 October 2022 Research evaluation Institutional archive of research Open science Evaluation and results of the research Via Università 40, 09124, Cagliari tel. 0706751 C.F.: 80019600925 P.I.: 00443370929 Certified e-mail Accessibility statement Site map Transparent administration HRS4R Strategy Our contacts Accessibility Wi-Fi Cookie policy Cookie settings Privacy Follow us",
