        "content": "Do plant biostimulants affect the survival of Escherichia coli in lettuce? | UnitusOpen Skip navigation Home Communities & Collections Research Outputs Researchers Organizations Projects Explore by Research Outputs Researchers Organizations Projects Help Sign on to: My DSpace Receive email updates Edit Account details Italiano English UnitusOpen Welcome in UnitusOpen, the institutional repository and open access archive of the University of Tuscia. UnitusOpen is the official channel of the University of Tuscia for collecting, archiving, and disseminating the scientific outputs of the researchers. Visitors of UnitusOpen may get access to open scientific outputs disseminated in accordance with the European requirements of Open Access or enter in contact with researchers for requesting information about their publications. UnitusOpen Prodotti della ricerca A. Contributo su rivista A1. Articolo in rivista Please use this identifier to cite or link to this item: http://hdl.handle.net/2067/52670 Title: Do plant biostimulants affect the survival of Escherichia coli in lettuce? Authors: FIORE, LEONARDO Cardarelli, Mariateresa Ruzzi, Maurizio Ficca, Anna Grazia Rouphael, Youssef Luziatelli, Francesca Colla, Giuseppe Journal: FRONTIERS IN PLANT SCIENCE Issue Date: 2024 Abstract: Considering that plant biostimulants can be sprayed multiple times on leafy crops even just before harvest, it is relevant to know the impact of biostimulant applications on Escherichia coli population dynamics of lettuce leaves to ensure food safety. Two trials were carried out to investigate whether the applications of a seaweed extract and a vegetal-derived protein hydrolysate (PH) could affect the E. coli growth in shake flasks (Exp. 1) and plant growth and survival of artificially inoculated E. coli on the leaf surface of lettuce grown in a floating system (Exp. 2). URI: http://hdl.handle.net/2067/52670 ISSN: 1664-462X DOI: 10.3389/fpls.2024.1495463 Appears in Collections: A1.