        "content": "Open science | University of Cagliari Skip to main content MUR - Italian Ministry of Universities and Research Search Search field Search ITA Login UniCA Magazine Search Search Search University About us Organisation Faculties and Departments Centres and other facilities Regulations Sustainability Competitive Examinations and Tenders Teaching Programmes Training Orientation Enrolling at UniCa Right to study Studying at UniCa University life Post-graduate activities Research Research funding opportunities Research facilities NRRP Research evaluation International Studying abroad Studying at UniCa EDUC Alliance Staff mobility Research, cooperation and planning programmes Support for internationalisation HRS4R Strategy Erasmus Charter for Higher Education Society and territory Institutions and businesses Employment counselling Public engagement Inclusion University services Contacts, information and payments Student services Teaching and research staff Administrative staff Future students Students Graduates Staff Institutions and enterprises Login UniCA Magazine University Teaching Research Research funding opportunities Research facilities NRRP Research evaluation Institutional archive of research Open science Evaluation and results of the research International Society and territory University services Open science Home Research Research evaluation Open science \" Open science \" is a scientific process approach based on collaboration, open and timely sharing of results, means of disseminating knowledge based on digital networked technologies and transparent methods of validation and evaluation of research products» (from the National Open Science Plan ). Since 2015, the University of Cagliari has been pursuing the principles of open science and is committed to promoting full access to scientific literature ( University Policy on open access to scientific research ). In 2022, as part of the HRS4R strategy , the University, together with the other Universities of the EDUC Alliance defined a common framework of objectives for Open Science , which includes the fields of research infrastructure, research data, citizen science and research evaluation. To develop and promote its own institutional strategy, the university has appointed the Commission for Open Science Policies , which collaborates with the Commission for Open Access to Scientific Literature on Open Access Policies. In 2024, UNICA adopted the \"University Policy for Open Science\" . The University of Cagliari has joined the CoARA coalition and signed the San Francisco DORA declaration, initiatives both related to research assessment. Open access to publications UniCa pursues the aims of open access: - through the establishment and maintenance of the institutional archive of the UNICA IRIS research products; - through the publishing services of its own publishing house, UNICApress , and the management of the UniCA Open Journals platform; - through incentives and facilitated conditions for open access publishing with scientific publishers (such as transformative contracts , as well as other discounts and agreements ). In 2022, the University's policies on open access to scientific research were approved: the basic concepts were set out, as well as the definitions and the practices to be followed in order to comply with Open Access publication standards. Open science: learn more Open Science event on 27 October 2023 Open Access event on 26 October 2022 Research evaluation Institutional archive of research Open science Evaluation and results of the research Via Università 40, 09124, Cagliari tel. 0706751 C.F.: 80019600925 P.I.: 00443370929 Certified e-mail Accessibility statement Site map Transparent administration HRS4R Strategy Our contacts Accessibility Wi-Fi Cookie policy Cookie settings Privacy Follow us",
